# Implementation Plan - Fix Minecraft 1.19+ Launch Issue

The goal is to fix the issue where Minecraft 1.19.1+ fails to launch. The identified cause is missing `log4j` configuration handling, which is required by newer Minecraft versions.

## Proposed Changes

### GeminiLauncher/Models

#### [MODIFY] [GameInstance.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Models/GameInstance.cs)
- Add `LogConfig` class to represent the logging configuration from `version.json`.
- Add `LogConfig` property to [GameInstance](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Models/GameInstance.cs#5-34).

```csharp
    public class GameInstance
    {
        // ... existing properties ...
        public LogConfig? LogConfig { get; set; }
    }

    public class LogConfig
    {
        public string Argument { get; set; } = string.Empty;
        public LogFile File { get; set; } = new LogFile();
        public string Type { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    }

    public class LogFile
    {
        public string Id { get; set; } = string.Empty;
        public string Sha1 { get; set; } = string.Empty;
        public long Size { get; set; }
        public string Url { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    }
```

### GeminiLauncher/Services

#### [MODIFY] [GameService.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/GameService.cs)
- Update [ParseVersionJson](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/GameService.cs#46-178) to parse the `logging` section.
- Implement `ParseLogging` helper method.

#### [MODIFY] [LaunchService.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/LaunchService.cs)
- In [ValidateAndRepairAsync](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/LaunchService.cs#451-530):
    - Check if `LogConfig` exists.
    - If so, check if the log config file (XML) exists at `assets/log_configs/<id>`.
    - If missing, add to download requests.
- In [LaunchGameAsync](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/LaunchService.cs#23-418):
    - If `LogConfig` is present, resolve the path to the log config file.
    - Add the JVM argument specified in `LogConfig.Argument` (replacing `${path}` with the absolute path).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- None available for this specific launch logic.

### Manual Verification
1.  **Launch 1.19.1**:
    - Select Minecraft 1.19.1 in the launcher.
    - Click "Start".
    - Verify that the game window appears.
    - Verify that `assets/log_configs/client-1.12.xml` (or similar) is downloaded.
    - Check `debug_launch_cmd.txt` to see if `-Dlog4j.configurationFile=...` is present.
2.  **Launch Older Version (e.g., 1.8.9)**:
    - Select a version that doesn't use `logging` config (or uses older format if any).
    - Click "Start".
    - Verify it still launches correctly (regression test).
